    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Global Warming: Not a Fantasy</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rachael Ludwick letter says Kyoto Protocol is based on weak science, with climate models based on computer models and land-based data rather than balloons and satellites (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Beware of the Kyoto Compromise'' (Op-Ed, Jan. 13): It is refreshing to hear the Kyoto treaty denounced openly. The most important point about the treaty is that it is based on very weak science. For example, the climate models that it relies on are based primarily on computer models and land-based data. These data are not as accurate as data gathered from balloons and satellites that  can be taken more evenly around the world at a variety of elevations that are not skewed by local city heating.</p>
        <p>RACHAEL LUDWICK  Tucson, Ariz., Jan. 13, 1999</p>
      </block>
